CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 5, 1966, pg. 1B reads: "Royal Pair - One of the highlights of the Dynamic Danettes' Mardi Gras, was the presentation of a king and queen who reigned over festivities. Mrs. Lydia Phillips was crowned "Queen" and Thomas Alexander, "King."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of "King" Thomas Alexander and "Queen" Lydia Phillips, seated in front of five women, including Alma Speed Fox second from right, and three men, including Bill Powell on right, posed in ballroom of Roosevelt Hotel for Danettes Mardi Gras Ball
